.TH "batadv_dat_check_dhcp_ipudp" 9 "batadv_dat_check_dhcp_ipudp" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_dat_check_dhcp_ipudp \- check skb for IP+UDP headers valid for DHCP
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" batadv_dat_check_dhcp_ipudp
.BI "(struct sk_buff *skb "  ","
.BI "__be32 *ip_src "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "skb" 12
the packet to check
.IP "ip_src" 12
a buffer to store the IPv4 source address in
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Checks whether the given skb has an IP and UDP header valid for a DHCP
message from a DHCP server. And if so, stores the IPv4 source address in
the provided buffer.
.SH "RETURN"
True if valid, false otherwise.
